snippet.textDisplay: If it were up to Indian composers, they would insert rap in sufi songs and ghazals as well. There is a reason why Coke studio India doesn't get much traction like our counterparts from across the border. They are still holding on to their traditional music and the fusion is kept to the minimum, while our composers are unnecessarily ruining the vibe of the song with being too westernized in their approach. This song too would get lost in 1 week time.
